Definition: a physical theory of relativity based on the assumption that the speed of light in a vacuum is a constant and the assumption that the laws of physics are invariant in all inertial systems
Synonyms: special_theory_of_relativity, special_relativity_theory, Einstein, s_special_theory_of_relativity, relativity, a, physical, theory, of, based, on, the, assumption, that, speed, light, in, vacuum, is, constant, and, laws, physics, are, invariant, all, inertial, systems
Category: noun.cognition
